
[Richmond, 16? June 1780. JHD, May 1780, 1827 edn., p. 50 (16 June): The Speaker laid before the House, a letter from the Governor, enclosing several letters and papers from a committee of Congress, on the present state of the army. Not located. Enclosures: presumably the Committee of Congress at Headquarters two letters to TJ of 25 May [451] 1780, q.v.; that of 2 June was apparently not transmitted until 19 June.]
